      "span_text": "Asthma results from complex interactions among inflammatory cells, their mediators, air-way epithelium and smooth muscle, and the nervous system. In genetically susceptible individuals, these interactions can lead the patient with asthma to symptoms of breathlessness, wheezing, cough, and chest tightness [CITATION_1] ."
